âš¡ 2. Number & Math Methods in JavaScript (Used in Projects)
âœ… Number Object Methods

// <------------------------------------------------>

Number.isInteger(value) â†’ check integer

Number.isFinite(value) â†’ check finite number

Number.isNaN(value) â†’ strict NaN check

Number.parseInt(str, base) â†’ convert string to integer (supports binary, hex, etc.)

Number.parseFloat(str) â†’ convert string to float

num.toFixed(n) â†’ fix decimal places (3.14159.toFixed(2) â†’ 3.14)

num.toPrecision(n) â†’ round to significant digits -------------------------> important

num.toExponential(n) â†’ scientific notation

num.toString(base) â†’ convert to binary/hex ((10).toString(2) â†’ "1010")


âœ… Math Object Methods (Most Used)

// <============================================>

Math.abs(x) â†’ absolute value -------------------> important

Math.round(x) â†’ nearest integer ---------------------------------------> important

Math.floor(x) â†’ round down----------------------------------> important

Math.ceil(x) â†’ round up  ------------------------------->important

Math.trunc(x) â†’ remove decimal part 

Math.min(a, b, ...) / Math.max(a, b, ...) â†’ smallest/largest number

Math.sqrt(x) â†’ square root

Math.cbrt(x) â†’ cube root

Math.pow(x, y) â†’ power

Math.sign(x) â†’ sign of number (-1, 0, 1)

Math.random() â†’ random number [0, 1) -------------------------------------> important
Math.log(x) â†’ natural log

Math.log10(x) / Math.log2(x) â†’ log base 10 / 2

Math.sin(), Math.cos(), Math.tan() â†’ trig functions

Math.hypot(x, y) â†’ âˆš(xÂ² + yÂ²) (useful in distance calcs)

